-- aditi.code: Code for  `-- Quote-4`
lang: ftd

\-- whitey4: -- Robert Bringhurst

"Big type, even huge type, can be beautiful and useful. But
poise is usually far more important than size – and poise
consists primarily of emptiness. Typographically, poise
is made of white space."





-- whitey4: -- Robert Bringhurst


"Big type, even huge type, can be beautiful and useful. But

poise is usually far more important than size – and poise

consists primarily of emptiness. Typographically, poise

is made of white space."










-- aditi.code: Code for  `-- Quote-5`
lang: ftd

\-- whitey5:

"There is a quote."
"There is an other quote."
"Guess what, A quote."
"Ahem... This is not even a quote"





-- whitey5:

"There is a quote."

"There is an other quote."

"Guess what, A quote."

"Ahem... This is not even a quote"










-- aditi.code: Code for  `-- Quote-6`
lang: ftd

\-- whitey6: JACQUES-YVES COUSTEAU

"What is a scientist after all?
It is a curious man looking through
a keyhole, the keyhole of nature,
trying to know what's going on."





-- whitey6: JACQUES-YVES COUSTEAU

"What is a scientist after all?

It is a curious man looking through

a keyhole, the keyhole of nature,

trying to know what's going on."










